  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Preventing and Reducing the Impact of HIV in South Sudan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Over 100 health providers have been trained to provide client-initiated testing and counseling (CICT) and provider-initiated testing and counseling (PITC) services, which are being offered in 17 sites. Three sites are providing PMTCT services for pregnant mothers and their infants. Additional project activities include HIV testing for pregnant women at ANC and maternity wards; ART for HIV-positive mothers; behavior change communication; and condom promotion and distribution. IntraHealth continues to play a critical role in establishing health and M&amp;amp;E systems in South Sudan by providing technical assistance in development of key HIV and M&amp;amp;E guidelines and tools and participating in HIV and M&amp;amp;E technical working groups. IntraHealth has also supported government implementation of HIV sentinel surveillance and development of a national HIV/AIDS policy</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project focuses on the prevention of HIV/AIDS transmission and on increasing access to services in two states, Central Equatoria and Eastern Equatoria</narrative>
  </description>
